sql:
SELECT min_value, max_value, mean_value, median_value
FROM column_statistics
WHERE column_id = 3 AND is_active = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "Most industrious bee in the garden" is a metaphor for the user who generates the most reports and spends the most time on them; 
- "Buzzing around to generate and tend to the most reports" refers to the user generating reports and being active in doing so;
- "Keeping the longest duration spent on report generation" refers to the total time spent generating reports;
- "Confined to the active reports in database one" implies filtering reports based on their active status and the database they belong to.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT user_id
FROM reports
WHERE report_type = 'summary';

SELECT databases.database_name, tables.table_name
FROM databases
JOIN tables ON databases.database_id = tables.database_id;

SELECT column_id 
FROM columns 
WHERE table_id = 'desired_table_id';

SELECT c.column_name
FROM columns c
WHERE c.column_id IN (
    SELECT column_id 
    FROM reports
)
AND c.column_id NOT IN (
    SELECT column_id 
    FROM data_analysis 
);

external_knowledge:
- "seas of data" refers to databases;
- "ships" refers to tables;
- "treasure" refers to the results of data analysis;
- "middle ground" is a metaphor for the median value in statistical analysis.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM databases 
WHERE is_active = 1;

SELECT column_id, mean_value, std_dev
FROM column_statistics
ORDER BY column_id ASC;

external_knowledge:
- "gardens" metaphorically refers to "databases";
- "keepers who nurture them" metaphorically refers to "users" who own the databases;
- "blossoming flowers within each garden" metaphorically refers to "tables" within each database.
